<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,224,503]" box="[151,586,224,251]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,224,251]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
145.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,224,503]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,260,287]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Distribution.</emphasis>
Restricted to central and western parts of Europe. 
<collectingCountry box="[928,1027,261,287]" name="Portugal" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: all 11 provinces (also Dyte unpubl. data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,224,503]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,333,359]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Ecology.</emphasis>
This species clearly prefers forests and mountainous habitats in 
<collectingCountry box="[1031,1129,333,359]" name="Portugal" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, and has not been recorded from the littoral zone. In northwestern Europe, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1941" box="[689,821,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Medetera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saxatilis">
<emphasis box="[689,821,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">M. saxatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found in numbers both in coastal and inland dunes, on trunks of a variety of deciduous trees and on walls.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,224,503]" box="[199,701,440,467]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,440,467]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
31.0 (common). Common (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,224,503]" box="[199,589,476,503]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,476,503]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Activity period.</emphasis>
April–November.
</paragraph>
